%h2
  Changing text formatting:
  
%p
  If you want to modify the way your text will appear&#8212;such as making parts of it bold or italicized&#8212;you can use a basic language called
  %em
    Textile.
    
%p
  To apply Textile to your text, you need to add characters (modifiers) to either side of the word or phrase you want to change, i.e.:
  
%table{:summary => "Textile Commands"}
  %tr
    %th{:width => "33%"}
      Formatting
    %th{:width => "33%"}
      Textile modifiers
    %th{:width => "33%"}
      Result
      
  %tr
    %th
      Bold
    %td
      This is *bold* text
    %td
      This is <strong>bold</strong> text
      
  %tr
    %th
      Italic
    %td
      This is _italic_ text
    %td
      This is <em>italic</em> text
      
  %tr
    %th
      Underline
    %td
      You can +underline+ text too
    %td
      You can <u>underline</u> text too
      
  %tr
    %th
      Strikethrough
    %td
      Or -strikethrough- text
    %td
      Or <s>strikethrough</s> text
      
  %tr
    %th
      Superscript
    %td
      Text can be ^superscript^
    %td
      Text can be <sup>superscript</sup>
      
  %tr
    %th
      Subscript
    %td
      Or it can be ~subscript~
    %td
      Or it can be <sub>subscript</sub>
      
      
%h2
  Headings in Textile

      
%p
  Some textile commands, such as headings, don't need to be added around an item, and can just be added at the start.
  
%table{:summary => "Textile Commands"}
  %tr
    %th{:width => "33%"}
      Formatting
    %th{:width => "33%"}
      Textile modifiers
    %th{:width => "33%"}
      Result
      
  %tr
    %th
      H1 Heading
    %td
      h1. This is a "H1" (largest and most important) heading
    %td
      %span{:style => "font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;"}
        This is a "H1" (largest and most important) heading
      
  %tr
    %th
      H2 Heading
    %td
      h2. This is a "H2" (second most important) heading
    %td
      %span{:style => "font-size: 1.3em; font-weight: bold;"}
        This is a "H2" (second most important) heading
      
  %tr
    %th
      H3 Heading
    %td
      h3. This is a "H3" (third most important) heading
    %td
      %span{:style => "font-size: 1.1em; font-weight: bold;"}
        This is a "H3" (third most important) heading
        
        
